=============
sinntp manual
=============

Description
===========

``sinntp`` is a tiny non-interactive NNTP client.


Global options
==============

--version                         show program's version number and exit
-h, --help                        show help message
-s, --syslog                      use syslog for logging
-v, --verbose                     be more verbose
-q, --quiet                       be quiet
-p PLUGIN, --plugin=PLUGIN        use plugin
-S SERVER, --server=SERVER        specify server address
-U USERNAME, --username=USERNAME  specify username
-P PASSWORD, --password=PASSWORD  specify password
-t TIMEOUT, --timeout=TIMEOUT     specify connection timeout
  

Commands
========

``pull``
--------
Fetch messages from the server and save them into the mailbox.
    
Arguments
`````````
Every argument is supposed to be a name of group, optionally followed by
a '``>``' character and mbox filename.

Options
```````
--limit=N   pull at most N messages
--reget     start from the first available message

Plugins
```````
mimify
    Add default charset to the message when it is not present.
    
``push``
--------
Send message from stdin to the server. Destination groups should be specified
in the ``Newsgroups:`` header or provided as command-line arguments if the
``Newsgroups:`` header is missing.

Arguments
`````````
Every argument is used as a destination newsgroup. Those arguments are ignored
if a ``Newsgroups:`` header is present in the message.

Options
```````
This command has no options.

Plugins
```````
strip_headers
    Strip specifed headers from message.

Environment variables
=====================

``NNTPSERVER``
    This variable specifies default server. It can be overriden by ``-S``
    option.

``SINNTP_HOME``
    This variable specifies the root directory for ``sinntp`` (default:
    ``~/.sinntp/``)


Files
=====

``/etc/news/server``
    A file with NNTP server address. Can be overriden by ``NNTPSERVER`` or
    ``-S`` option.


